summary: He knows that Arya and Gendry were in love with him long before they even realized it.  It started one day, trying to traverse...
body:
He knows that Arya and Gendry were in love with him long before they even realized it. 

It started one day, trying to traverse up the slippery stairs of Winterfell. The soles of his boots were worn-out and ragged, and he had meant to get them replaced. After all, he wouldn’t want to go down in history being the fool who tripped and fell because his boots were not maintained.

“What’s wrong?” Arya had mocked, her grey eyes lit up with humor. “The all-powerful Targaryen prince can’t even climb the stairs without needing help?”

Gendry didn’t say anything, but he didn’t bother hiding the smirk dancing on his lips either. 

These two were the most insolent pair he has ever met. And he loved them for it. 

“Quiet.” He scowled back, trying to retain his dignity. As if the gods were taunting him and out to ruin his life, he felt his right boot slipped slightly under the icy edge. 

“Careful!” Arya yelped.

Gendry was quicker to react, standing right beside him. It wasn’t a terrible or noticeable mishap, and if Arya hadn’t shouted like that, no one would have even noticed it. But Arya’s yell had alerted Daenerys, who turned around in confusion. 

“I think,” Gendry’s voice was quiet, laced with amusement. “That our prince may require some help.”

Arya had let out a loud sigh, but the smile on her face was not of annoyance but of indulgence. “Oh, alright. Come on then, Aegon.”

As if the gods were trying to ruin his life further, they both extended their hands out towards him at the same time. He stared at their hands, and then at their faces. 

“Well?” Gendry prodded. 

Daenerys’ brow was climbing up to her hairline, and he was thankful that Jon was not present at least. 

He slipped his hands in theirs, feeling his heart beat rapidly in his chest. Even through the gloves, their hands were so warm. 

He hated how unaffected the both of them were. He hated how they damned propriety, never shy with their touches and affection. He hated how they would stare at him, as if he hung the stars in the night sky, and then enclosed each other in a bubble of their own, with no way in for anyone but themselves. He hated how he couldn’t even muster up the slightest hint of anger for that, because they both loved each other so much, and he’s already content with the way they looked at him.
